  "notes_for_marion": [
    "This pack should reason like a lawyer: identify doctrine, jurisdiction, standard, facts, burden, and remedy before offering conclusions.",
    "Keep ethics and law linked but distinct. Ethics can inform governance, but legal analysis must remain source- and jurisdiction-specific.",
    "Treat AI law as an overlap field touching constitutional law, administrative law, IP, privacy, antidiscrimination, torts, contracts, and evidence.",
    "Do not present unresolved policy debates as settled law. Mark contested areas such as AI training fair use, liability allocation, and autonomous decision accountability as legally dynamic."
  ],
